[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brendan Galloway: West Brom sign Everton defender on loan

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
West Bromwich Albion have signed left-back Brendan Galloway from Premier League rivals Everton on a season-long loan deal, with no recall option.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Zimbabwe-born 20-year-old, who has played for England's youth teams up to Under-19 level, began his career as a trainee at Milton Keynes Dons.
He has made 21 appearances for Everton, including 16 starts in the top flight.
"It's really important to gain more experience. Coming here is the perfect opportunity to do that," Galloway said.
